23#pragma once
24
25#include "CachedResource.h"
26#include "Image.h"
27#include "ImageObserver.h"
28#include "IntRect.h"
29#include "IntSizeHash.h"
30#include "LayoutSize.h"

34namespace WebCore {
35
36class CachedImageClient;
37class CachedResourceLoader;
38class FloatSize;
39class MemoryCache;
40class RenderElement;
41class RenderObject;
42class SecurityOrigin;
43
44struct Length;
45
46class CachedImage final : public CachedResource {
47 friend class MemoryCache;
48
49public:
50 CachedImage(CachedResourceRequest&&, PAL::SessionID, const CookieJar*);
51 CachedImage(Image*, PAL::SessionID, const CookieJar*);
52 // Constructor to use for manually cached images.
53 CachedImage(const URL&, Image*, PAL::SessionID, const CookieJar*, const String& domainForCachePartition);
54 virtual ~CachedImage();
55
56 WEBCORE_EXPORT Image* image(); // Returns the nullImage() if the image is not available yet.
57 WEBCORE_EXPORT Image* imageForRenderer(const RenderObject*); // Returns the nullImage() if the image is not available yet.
58 bool hasImage() const { return m_image.get(); }
59 bool hasSVGImage() const;
60 bool currentFrameKnownToBeOpaque(const RenderElement*);
61
62 std::pair<Image*, float> brokenImage(float deviceScaleFactor) const; // Returns an image and the image's resolution scale factor.
63 bool willPaintBrokenImage() const;
64
65 bool canRender(const RenderElement* renderer, float multiplier) { return !errorOccurred() && !imageSizeForRenderer(renderer, multiplier).isEmpty(); }
66
67 void setContainerContextForClient(const CachedImageClient&, const LayoutSize&, float, const URL&);
68 bool usesImageContainerSize() const { return m_image && m_image->usesContainerSize(); }
69 bool imageHasRelativeWidth() const { return m_image && m_image->hasRelativeWidth(); }
70 bool imageHasRelativeHeight() const { return m_image && m_image->hasRelativeHeight(); }
71
72 void updateBuffer(SharedBuffer&) override;
73 void finishLoading(SharedBuffer*, const NetworkLoadMetrics&) override;
74
75 enum SizeType {
76 UsedSize,
77 IntrinsicSize
78 };
79 WEBCORE_EXPORT FloatSize imageSizeForRenderer(const RenderElement* renderer, SizeType = UsedSize) const;
80 // This method takes a zoom multiplier that can be used to increase the natural size of the image by the zoom.
81 LayoutSize imageSizeForRenderer(const RenderElement*, float multiplier, SizeType = UsedSize) const; // returns the size of the complete image.
82 LayoutSize unclampedImageSizeForRenderer(const RenderElement* renderer, float multiplier, SizeType = UsedSize) const;
83 void computeIntrinsicDimensions(Length& intrinsicWidth, Length& intrinsicHeight, FloatSize& intrinsicRatio);
84
85 bool isManuallyCached() const { return m_isManuallyCached; }
86 RevalidationDecision makeRevalidationDecision(CachePolicy) const override;
87 void load(CachedResourceLoader&) override;
88
89 bool isOriginClean(SecurityOrigin*);
90
91 bool isClientWaitingForAsyncDecoding(CachedImageClient&) const;
92 void addClientWaitingForAsyncDecoding(CachedImageClient&);
93 void removeAllClientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding();
94
95 void setForceUpdateImageDataEnabledForTesting(bool enabled) { m_forceUpdateImageDataEnabledForTesting = enabled; }
96
97 bool stillNeedsLoad() const override { return !errorOccurred() && status() == Unknown && !isLoading(); }
98 bool canSkipRevalidation(const CachedResourceLoader&, const CachedResourceRequest&) const;
99
100 bool isVisibleInViewport(const Document&) const;
101
102private:
103 void clear();
104
105 CachedImage(CachedImage&, const ResourceRequest&, PAL::SessionID);
106
107 void setBodyDataFrom(const CachedResource&) final;
108
109 bool isPDFResource() const;
110 bool isPostScriptResource() const;
111
112 void createImage();
113 void clearImage();
114 // If not null, changeRect is the changed part of the image.
115 void notifyObservers(const IntRect* changeRect = nullptr);
116 void checkShouldPaintBrokenImage();
117
118 void switchClientsToRevalidatedResource() final;
119 bool mayTryReplaceEncodedData() const final { return true; }
120
121 void didAddClient(CachedResourceClient&) final;
122 void didRemoveClient(CachedResourceClient&) final;
123
124 void allClientsRemoved() override;
125 void destroyDecodedData() override;
126
127 bool shouldDeferUpdateImageData() const;
128 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> convertedDataIfNeeded(SharedBuffer* data) const;
129 void didUpdateImageData();
130 EncodedDataStatus updateImageData(bool allDataReceived);
131 void updateData(const uint8_t* data, unsigned length) override;
132 void error(CachedResource::Status) override;
133 void responseReceived(const ResourceResponse&) override;
134
135 // For compatibility, images keep loading even if there are HTTP errors.
136 bool shouldIgnoreHTTPStatusCodeErrors() const override { return true; }
137
138 class CachedImageObserver final : public RefCounted<CachedImageObserver>, public ImageObserver {
139 public:
140 static Ref<CachedImageObserver> create(CachedImage& image) { return adoptRef(*new CachedImageObserver(image)); }
141 HashSet<CachedImage*>& cachedImages() { return m_cachedImages; }
142 const HashSet<CachedImage*>& cachedImages() const { return m_cachedImages; }
143
144 private:
145 explicit CachedImageObserver(CachedImage&);
146
147 // ImageObserver API
148 URL sourceUrl() const override { return !m_cachedImages.isEmpty() ? (*m_cachedImages.begin())->url() : URL(); }
149 String mimeType() const override { return !m_cachedImages.isEmpty() ? (*m_cachedImages.begin())->mimeType() : emptyString(); }
150 long long expectedContentLength() const override { return !m_cachedImages.isEmpty() ? (*m_cachedImages.begin())->expectedContentLength() : 0; }
151
152 void encodedDataStatusChanged(const Image&, EncodedDataStatus) final;
153 void decodedSizeChanged(const Image&, long long delta) final;
154 void didDraw(const Image&) final;
155
156 bool canDestroyDecodedData(const Image&) final;
157 void imageFrameAvailable(const Image&, ImageAnimatingState, const IntRect* changeRect = nullptr, DecodingStatus = DecodingStatus::Invalid) final;
158 void changedInRect(const Image&, const IntRect*) final;
159 void scheduleRenderingUpdate(const Image&) final;
160
161 HashSet<CachedImage*> m_cachedImages;
162 };
163
164 void encodedDataStatusChanged(const Image&, EncodedDataStatus);
165 void decodedSizeChanged(const Image&, long long delta);
166 void didDraw(const Image&);
167 bool canDestroyDecodedData(const Image&);
168 void imageFrameAvailable(const Image&, ImageAnimatingState, const IntRect* changeRect = nullptr, DecodingStatus = DecodingStatus::Invalid);
169 void changedInRect(const Image&, const IntRect*);
170 void scheduleRenderingUpdate(const Image&);
171
172 void updateBufferInternal(SharedBuffer&);
173
174 void didReplaceSharedBufferContents() override;
175
176 struct ContainerContext {
177 LayoutSize containerSize;
178 float containerZoom;
179 URL imageURL;
180 };
181
182 using ContainerContextRequests = HashMap<const CachedImageClient*, ContainerContext>;
183 ContainerContextRequests m_pendingContainerContextRequests;
184
185 HashSet<CachedImageClient*> m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding;
186
187 RefPtr<CachedImageObserver> m_imageObserver;
188 RefPtr<Image> m_image;
189 std::unique_ptr<SVGImageCache> m_svgImageCache;
190
191 MonotonicTime m_lastUpdateImageDataTime;
192
193 WeakPtr<Document> m_skippingRevalidationDocument;
194
195 static constexpr unsigned maxUpdateImageDataCount = 4;
196 unsigned m_updateImageDataCount : 3;
197 bool m_isManuallyCached : 1;
198 bool m_shouldPaintBrokenImage : 1;
199 bool m_forceUpdateImageDataEnabledForTesting : 1;
200};
201
202} // namespace WebCore
